<div id="top-content">
  <div class="heading-with-actions top-heading">
    <h1>
      <span translate="no">wxTextAttr</span> 
      <small class="app-vsn" translate="no">(wx v2.5.4)</small>

    </h1>

<a href="wxTextAttr.md" title="Copy Markdown (hold Ctrl/Cmd and click it to open as Markdown)" class="copy-markdown icon-action" rel="help">
  <i class="ri-markdown-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
  <span class="sr-only">Copy Markdown</span>
</a>



      <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/wx/src/gen/wxTextAttr.erl#L58" title="View Source" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow">
        <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
        <span class="sr-only">View Source</span>
      </a>

  </div>


    <section id="moduledoc">
<p><a href="wxTextAttr.html"><code class="inline">wxTextAttr</code></a> represents the character and paragraph attributes, or style, for a range
of text in a <a href="wxTextCtrl.html"><code class="inline">wxTextCtrl</code></a> or <code class="inline">wxRichTextCtrl</code> (not implemented in wx).</p><p>When setting up a <a href="wxTextAttr.html"><code class="inline">wxTextAttr</code></a> object, pass a bitlist mask to <a href="#setFlags/2"><code class="inline">setFlags/2</code></a> to indicate which style
elements should be changed. As a convenience, when you call a setter such as SetFont, the
relevant bit will be set.</p><p>See: <a href="wxTextCtrl.html"><code class="inline">wxTextCtrl</code></a></p><p>wxWidgets docs: <a rel="nofollow" href="https://docs.wxwidgets.org/3.2/classwx_text_attr.html">wxTextAttr</a></p>
    </section>

</div>

